11/01/2005
SOFIA, Bulgaria -- The government's Council for NATO Integration adopted changes Monday (10 January) aimed at separating the political and military aspects of the NATO-related decision-making process.
Deputy Prime Minister Plamen Panayotov, who heads the panel, said the changes include holding Council sessions in three formats -- operational, basic or enlarged -- with the participation of cabinet ministers, army representatives, advisers to the president and heads of the special services determined accordingly.
The changes were forwarded to the Council of Ministers for approval.
(Dnevnik, Sega - 11/01/05)
